ence-based.Key FeaturesProvides a historical overview of assessment and feedback in universities showing how our understanding of assessment practices has changed over the years, both in response to new conceptualisations of learning and the changing nature of societyContains new perspectives of assessment and feedback provided by world renowned researchers on issues that are currently of great interest to both academic managers and teaching staffReports on recent innovations in assessment practices in higher educationEngages critically with recent research on assessment and feedback offering evidence-based conclusions"  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aEducation, Higher. 0aGrading and marking. 4aPolitics. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh1 aAnderson, Charles, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aAnderson, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoud, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEntwistle, Noel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aEntwistle, Noel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFawns, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHailikari, Telle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaragiannopoulou, Evangelia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKreber, Carolin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLindblom-Ylänne, Sari, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcArthur, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCune, Velda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcDowell, Liz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ct